00:47:25.335 --> 00:47:26.210
ERIC WEINER: Correct.

00:47:26.210 --> 00:47:27.001
AUDIENCE: --genius.

00:47:27.001 --> 00:47:29.400
And obviously the eighth
chapter is about Silicon Valley,

00:47:29.400 --> 00:47:30.540
which is still ongoing.

00:47:30.540 --> 00:47:33.060
What do you see from your
visits out there, and looking

00:47:33.060 --> 00:47:36.990
at the previous seven examples,
are the threats to having

00:47:36.990 --> 00:47:38.270
it end in Silicon Valley?

00:47:38.270 --> 00:47:39.355
That period of genius.

00:47:39.355 --> 00:47:41.477
Is there something, one,
or two, three, things

00:47:41.477 --> 00:47:43.560
that you see are early
indicators that something's

00:47:43.560 --> 00:47:44.690
going wrong?

00:47:44.690 --> 00:47:46.672
ERIC WEINER: That's
a very good question.

00:47:46.672 --> 00:47:48.130
First of all, the
idea of it ending

00:47:48.130 --> 00:47:51.380
is not out of the question,
because these golden ages

00:47:51.380 --> 00:47:55.330
tend to last a few decades,
maybe half a century, maybe

00:47:55.330 --> 00:47:58.140
a century at the outside.

00:47:58.140 --> 00:48:00.200
Rarely did they
see the end coming.

00:48:00.200 --> 00:48:03.210
I don't think anyone in Detroit
in the '30s, '40s, and '50s,

00:48:03.210 --> 00:48:05.300
saw the end coming.

00:48:05.300 --> 00:48:08.280
I think the biggest threat
can be summed up in one word,

00:48:08.280 --> 00:48:09.940
and that's arrogance.

00:48:09.940 --> 00:48:12.960
I think if you become
arrogant, you lack ignorance.

00:48:12.960 --> 00:48:15.150
You lack that humility.

00:48:15.150 --> 00:48:19.610
Which is, the humility of,
there's things I don't know.

00:48:19.610 --> 00:48:25.520
I think staying in one industry,
and being a one note town,

00:48:25.520 --> 00:48:28.419
albeit one that plays in
different keys, is dangerous.

00:48:28.419 --> 00:48:30.460
All these other places I
looked at, historically,

00:48:30.460 --> 00:48:33.080
were pretty much,
with the exception

00:48:33.080 --> 00:48:39.280
of Vienna in the 1700s with
music, were interdisciplinary.

00:48:39.280 --> 00:48:40.480
There was a lot going on.

00:48:40.480 --> 00:48:44.080
And not only does that
diversify, spread out the risk,

00:48:44.080 --> 00:48:48.690
it also is more likely to have
different fields sparking off

00:48:48.690 --> 00:48:49.700
one another.

00:48:49.700 --> 00:48:51.940
Often a breakthrough
in one field like art,

00:48:51.940 --> 00:48:53.770
might lead to completely
a breakthrough

00:48:53.770 --> 00:49:00.010
in a completely unrelated field
like science, or technology.

00:49:00.010 --> 00:49:03.150
So I'm concerned
about arrogance,

00:49:03.150 --> 00:49:04.710
and I see some
signs of bling out

00:49:04.710 --> 00:49:06.940
there I hadn't seen
10 years ago, always

00:49:06.940 --> 00:49:09.220
the canary in the coal mine.

00:49:09.220 --> 00:49:12.760
And I'm concerned about
the specialization.

00:49:12.760 --> 00:49:14.460
Pixar is probably
the best example

00:49:14.460 --> 00:49:20.230
of combining Hollywood
and Silicon Valley.

00:49:20.230 --> 00:49:22.010
I would say those are
my two big concerns.

00:49:22.010 --> 00:49:24.720
But my theory on Silicon
Valley is that it has nothing

00:49:24.720 --> 00:49:26.590
to do with technology, really.

00:49:26.590 --> 00:49:28.870
The product is
technology, of course,

00:49:28.870 --> 00:49:33.020
but the process is
a creative ecology

00:49:33.020 --> 00:49:36.690
that's very good at
recognizing good ideas.

00:49:36.690 --> 00:49:38.810
Not really inventing
them, the cell phone,

00:49:38.810 --> 00:49:41.430
correct me if I'm wrong, was
not invented in Silicon Valley.

00:49:41.430 --> 00:49:45.050
And I even think venture
capital came from New York.

00:49:45.050 --> 00:49:48.820
But they're good at--
ideas aren't born there,

00:49:48.820 --> 00:49:51.500
they come of age there.

00:49:51.500 --> 00:49:56.070
If they remain good at that,
and good at importing ideas,

00:49:56.070 --> 00:49:58.360
they can stay fresh for
a little while, I think.

00:49:58.360 --> 00:50:00.930
